column5: Anybody fish this camp? How is the fishing/cabins/boats etc? I see they have some vacancies. I have never fished it. Just curious how the walleye fishing might be? Thanks.
Several past threads on this camp if you do a search. Overall very good reviews.

I was there oct 1 after they open the border,had the whole lake to myself,fishing was good,cabin was good,boat n old mercury 2 stroke worked fine,the road going back to the resort was a nightmare,very long and I could only go like 5mph,so if you go there make sure you have all your needs,you do not want to have to leave camp to go to Ignace to get something.

OP should touch base with dr. lee who posts on this site. He goes to Press regularly. One of my fishing companions went to Press a few years ago. Caught plenty, but mostly eaters. Like Eck said, tough road in.
Lots of eaters,nothing big,but only resort on the lake which is nice.The road will keep me from going back.

Thank you. I have seen several posts on facebook from them with vacancies so it made me wonder is all. thanks again. Gullrock for my the 1st week of Sept. Five lakes. Then again the 3rd week of sept. at the same place ....hopefully....depending on the daughters hockey schedule.
